"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(DISTINCT a.atom_id) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT m.molecule_id)) AS percentage\nFROM \n    molecule m\nJOIN \n    atom a ON m.molecule_id = a.molecule_id\nWHERE \n    a.element = 'cl' AND m.label = '+';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of chlorine atoms in carcinogenic molecules. It joins the `molecule` and `atom` tables on `molecule_id`, filters for chlorine atoms (`element = 'cl'`) and carcinogenic molecules (`label = '+'`), and computes the percentage of such atoms relative to the total number of carcinogenic molecules."